  "text": "For problems with a larger size, when many processors are available, parallel algorithms are used to break the complexity, this is the case for domain decomposition as we indicated in the introduction and the iterations of the algorithm can be intertwined with the iterations of the parareal algorithm. This is explained in the first subsection in the case of an overlapping domain decomposition. Of course non-overlapping domain decomposition (FETI, Neumann-Neumann...) can also be used as is presented in [CITATION_1] and into more details in [13] .",
